===Verb===
{{en-verb|bends|bending|bent|past2=bended|past2_qual=archaic}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause (something) to change its shape into a [[curve]], by [[physical]] [[force]], [[chemical]] action, or any other means. <!--accomplishment,achievement-->
#: ''If you '''bend''' the pipe too far, it will break.''
#: ''Don’t '''bend''' your knees.''
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To become [[curve]]d. <!--activity,accomplishment-->
#: ''Look at the trees '''bending''' in the wind.''
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause to change direction.
#* Milton
#*: '''Bend''' thine ear to supplication.
#* Shakespeare
#*: Towards Coventry '''bend''' we our course.
#* Sir Walter Scott
#*: '''bending''' her eyes {{...}} upon her parent
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To change direction. <!--state,activity-->
#: ''The road '''bends''' to the right''
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To be inclined; to direct itself.
